#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Completing Reconciliation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finishing Reconciliation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:211
#, no-c-format
msgid "When the difference between the statement and the cleared balance is zero, then the account is reconciled and you can click <guibutton>Finish</guibutton>. When you do this, &kmymoney; takes all the transactions which have been marked as cleared (only those with a date before the statement date) and marks them as reconciled, and the value in the <guilabel>C</guilabel> column changes from <quote>C</quote> to <quote>R</quote>. In addition, it saves the changes and records that the account has been reconciled. (You still need to save the file to permanently save all the changes.)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:223
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Reconciliation Report"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid "The last thing the reconciliation wizard does it to present a report, in the form of a pop-up with two tabs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "Summary Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "This tab shows a summary of the reconciliation, including the starting and ending balances, and the number and amount of payments and deposits: cleared, outstanding, and those after the reconciliation date."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "Details Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "This tab shows a list of outstanding payments and charges. These are unmarked transactions prior to the statement date of the reconciliation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "Postponing Reconciliation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you're having trouble completing the reconciliation, or you need to gather additional information before you can complete the process, you can postpone the process to a later time by clicking <guibutton>Postpone</guibutton>. When you do this, &kmymoney; remembers the values you entered when you started the wizard, it does not mark cleared transactions as reconciled, and it returns the ledger to its normal view. If you exit &kmymoney; before clicking either <guibutton>Finish</guibutton> or <guibutton>Postpone</guibutton>, it has the same effect as clicking <guibutton>Postpone</guibutton>. Any edits you have made, such as marking transactions cleared or entering new transactions, are not touched, and you can still save them before you exit &kmymoney;. However, you will have to run the reconciliation wizard again in order to reconcile the account."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable5
#: details-reconciliation.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you do click <guilabel>Postpone</guilabel>, the next time you run the reconciliation wizard on this account, &kmymoney; remembers the values you entered when you previously ran the wizard, and you will be able to change them, if necessary. In this case, the initial screen of the wizard is different, to remind you of this."
msgstr ""

